The paper deals with the problem of mobile robots on a graph, which is a common topic in the field of robotics (cs.RO). The problem of dispersion on a graph is a graph algorithmic problem, which falls under the category of distributed computing (cs.DC) and graph theory (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the use of randomness in solving the problem, which is a common technique in the field of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the problem of mobile robot dispersion can also be seen as a problem in control theory (cs.SY).
